<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1295] Make some Dublin Core items multi-valued</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1295</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pdfa.org/2011/08/pdfa-metadata-xmp-rdf-dublin-core&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.pdfa.org/2011/08/pdfa-metadata-xmp-rdf-dublin-core&lt;/a&gt;, dc:title, dc:description and dc:rights should allow multiple values because of language alternatives.  Unless anyone objects in the next few days, I&apos;ll switch those to Property.toInternalTextBag() from Property.toInternalText().  I&apos;ll also modify PDFParser to extract dc:rights.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12713676">TIKA-1295</key>
            <summary>Make some Dublin Core items multi-valued</summary>
